		`3 The high priest asked Stephen, “Are these men telling the truth about you?” Stephen said “You people are stubborn and rebellious against God. You constantly reject the Holy Spirit, just as our ancestors constantly rejected God and killed his prophets. But you did something worse. You killed the Messiah!” And the people were deeply convicted in their hearts, but became angry.`
		`4 Stephen then received a vision from the Holy Spirit, and said "I see the heavens opened, and the Son of man standing on the right hand of God." When the religious leaders heard this, they were so angry that they covered their ears and yelled loudly. They dragged Stephen out of the city and threw stones at him in order to kill him.`
