		`8 God commanded Abraham to sacrifice his own son, Isaac to Him. Abraham obeyed God and almost sacrificed his son, but at the last second, God stopped him and provided a ram to die in the place of Isaac. God taught abraham that he will sacrifice his own Son, so that Abraham's descendants will live. That is why we call Jesus the Lamb of God.`
		`9 When God sent the last plague on Egypt, he told each Israelite family to kill a lamb. The lamb must not have any flaws. Then they had to spread its blood on their door frames. An angel would go and destroy every firstborn son, but it would passover those homes on which there was blood on their door frames. When this happened, God called this the Passover.`
		`10 The passover lamb was a symbol of Jesus. He was killed at the time of the Passover festival. Jesus never sinned, just as the lamb that had no flaws. To all who believe in Jesus, death will pass over them and will obtain eternal life . `
