		`12 Even if you do many good deeds, it cannot make you deserve eternal life. Every sin must be paid for by death. God will not allow sin and sinners to live forever because God is good, and sin is not. All people deserve to die, but if you repent of your sins, believe that Jesus died for your sins, and confess your sins to Him. God will consider your sin paid-for by Christ's death. Then, just as God resurrected Jesus from the dead, he will resurrect you and give you eternal life.`
		`13 God will save everyone who repents of sin, and believes in Jesus. But He will not save those who do not repent from sin. It does not matter if you are rich or poor, man or woman, old or young, or where you live. God loves you and wants you to repent and believe in Jesus so that you can live with him forever.`
		`14 Jesus is calling you to believe in him and to be baptized. Do you believe that Jesus is the Messiah, the only Son of God? Do you believe that you are a sinner and that you deserve death for your sin? Do you believe that Jesus died on the cross to take your place and wash away your sins?`
